Example of using CreDating

Xavier Didelot

2017-10-03

Initialisation

library(CreDating)
library(ape)
set.seed(0)

Data

We consider a random timed tree with 20 leaves, with the root in 2000.

nsam <- 20
phy <- rtree(nsam, br = rexp)
phy$root.time <- 2000
plot(phy)
axisPhylo(backward = F)

We can extract the sampling dates.

dates = leafDates(phy)

On each branch we observe a number of substitutions which is distributed \(\mathrm{Poisson}(rl)\) where \(l\) is the branch length and \(r=1\) per year is the real substitution rate.

obsphy=phy
obsphy$root.time=NULL
obsphy$edge.length=unlist(lapply(obsphy$edge.length*1,function (x) rpois(1,x)))
#obsphy$edge.length=unlist(lapply(obsphy$edge.length*10,function (x) rgamma(1,x,1)))
plot(obsphy)
axisPhylo(backward = F)

Lets do a root-to-tip regression analysis:

res=roottotip(obsphy,dates)

Analysis

We run CreDating as follows:

res=credating(obsphy,dates,nbIts = 1000,model=3,updateRate=1)
plot(res)

Plot with credibility bars:

plot(res,'treeCI')

We can see what the MCMC traces look like:

plot(res,'trace')
